OL,3,CLiverpool captain Virgil van Dijk says
OL,4,Che is 'dreading' Klopp exit
OL,6,FVan Dijk said if the new manager
OL,7,Fwanted advice he'd be happy to offer
OL,8,Fit, and he would encourage them to be
OL,9,Ftheir own man: "You want to do things
OL,10,Fin your own way, what you think is
OL,11,Fimportant for the team and what will
OL,12,Fbe successful to the team.
OL,14,F"That's what you bring to the table as
OL,15,Fwell.
OL,17,F"I'm sure that a new manager will
OL,18,Fdefinitely have that feeling but if
OL,19,Fthere's any questions or anything that
OL,20,Fhe would like me to advise him on I
OL,21,Fwould definitely do that."
